# Jongara File Structure and Organization

This rule defines the expected file structure and organization for the Jongara Flutter application. Follow this structure when creating new files or modifying existing ones.

## Core Layer
```
lib/core/
├── constants/
│   ├── app_constants.dart       # App-wide constants (colors, dimensions, etc.)
│   └── mahjong_constants.dart   # Mahjong-specific constants (tile types, layouts)
├── utils/
│   └── game_utils.dart          # Game utility functions
└── theme/
    └── app_theme.dart           # Theme definitions
```

## Data Layer
```
lib/data/
├── models/
│   ├── mahjong_tile_model.dart  # Mahjong tile data model
│   ├── game_state_model.dart    # Game state model
│   └── achievement_model.dart   # Achievement model
└── repositories/
    ├── game_repository.dart     # Game data repository implementation
    └── achievement_repository.dart # Achievement repository implementation
```

## Domain Layer
```
lib/domain/
├── entities/
│   ├── mahjong_tile_entity.dart # Mahjong tile business entity
│   └── game_entity.dart         # Game business entity
├── repositories/
│   └── game_repository_interface.dart # Repository interface
└── usecases/
    ├── generate_level_usecase.dart    # Level generation use case
    ├── check_match_usecase.dart       # Match checking use case
    └── update_selectable_tiles_usecase.dart # Tile selection use case
```

## Presentation Layer
```
lib/presentation/
├── pages/
│   ├── main_menu_page.dart      # Main menu screen
│   ├── level_selection_page.dart # Level selection screen
│   ├── game_board_page.dart     # Game board screen
│   ├── tips_page.dart           # Tips screen
│   └── achievements_page.dart   # Achievements screen
├── widgets/
│   ├── mahjong_tile_widget.dart # Mahjong tile widget
│   ├── hand_slot_widget.dart    # Hand slot widget
│   └── game_over_dialog.dart    # Game over dialog
└── viewmodels/
    └── game_viewmodel.dart      # Game view model
```

## Main Entry Point
```
lib/main.dart                    # Application entry point
```

Always place new files in the appropriate directory according to their responsibility and follow the established naming conventions.